sentences: Sierra Kay Kusterbeck (born December 18, 1990), better known as Sierra Kay, is an American singer-songwriter and model.
Kusterbeck auditioned to be VersaEmerge's lead vocalist in 2006, by sending a tape of herself singing one of VersaEmerge's songs, "The Blank Static Screen".
VersaEmerge released their first EP with Kusterbeck on vocals, Perceptions, in May 2008.
They were signed to Fueled by Ramen in 2008, and they released their self-titled EP in 2009 and their debut album Fixed at Zero the following year.

In 2016, Kay and Nick Fit of Trash Talk started the band Neaux (pronounced "nOH").
Described as an Indie/post-punk band, they released their debut album "Fell Off The Deep End" in 2016.
In August 2017, they announced the release of their second album, Chain Up The Sun, released on The Native Sounds.
